all of these points are true but they don’t matter

what actually matters: even though you and me, and mert, and zooko, etc etc etc, knew that secret inflation bugs are fundamentally one of the biggest structural risks to ZEC, virtually no one of the new generation of buyers knew about it

instead they were sold an insane narrative that ZEC is somehow safer than bitcoin (!!!!!)

instead of continuing to downplay the issue by focusing on the misinfo (which is largely unsubstantial anyway), it would be better to more openly explain the tradeoffs. i think it’s very likely that more bugs of this nature will be discovered in the near future by more advanced models, might as well explain the tradeoff thoroughly now instead of fact-checking some red herrings

i do empathize with how frustrating it is to hear this from me given that you’re genuinely a responsible and balanced guy and have been publicly posting nuanced takes all along

but i think you might be misunderstanding my point. we’re boomers now man. our role is no longer to post things. there are new, younger people who shape public opinion now, and none of us (or at zcash foundation etc or whatever those entities are called now) have been doing enough to make sure those people properly educate the market on the risks

