yes i am well aware that i sold cat jpegs

i never claimed that they were a better and safer store of value than bitcoin. people knew what they were buying: jpegs of cats

it’s not that bad, it is what it is, main reason for the panic is that the market didn’t price in that this kind of bug is a possibility 

now it has. this vulnerability almost certainly wasn’t exploited, people understand the risks better now, can continue building with reinforced information symmetry

@aBlock0 @EliBenSasson i’m sure shielded holders will be relieved to learn that an attacker can only steal what they put in the pool and not more

i am 99.99% sure the bug wasn’t exploited. IMO instead of playing short-term games reassuring the market that it wasn’t, zcash should play the long-term games of educating the market that bugs like this are always possible, and explaining why they believe the trade-off is worth it, so that next time opus 5.7 finds a bug people don’t have to panic all over again.

i have a lot of criticism for how the bitcoin community handles things but you can’t say that it’s hiding risks. for example the quntum risk is top of mind for everyone. i don’t like the reaction from core devs etc but the risks are known and disclosed and priced in. with zcash this risk just wasn’t understood by the market, and that’s a fact.

